observations.conclusion:
I wanted to identify but there was too much reliance on the form, working backwards.  I annotated many more features following comparison, a couple of which were of the 'rare' type. By evaluation stage I'd spent longer looking at the mark which gave my eyes time to get used to the nature of the ridges. Perhaps I should have spent more time at analysis stage to settle into the mark as I think I would have marked up more, particularly of the 'rare' type as they would definitely have influenced my conclusion if I'd noticed them at analysis.

Degree of similarity - 4

Degree of support - 3

(C) Degree of Similarity = 4
(E) Degree of Support = 5

Degree of similarity - medium
Degree of support - 4

There are a few differences in this comparison, however I think they are all explainable. The area down from the core I have done my best to pair minutiae, however I would prefer to avoid this area completely (marked 14-19). There is too much movement and distortion. 
Although some of the minutiae I have paired don't have high clarity, I can see that they do exist, I'm just not 100% sure on their location as the ridges are merging together in places. Some of the ridges 'peter out' into subsidiary ridges, also making it difficult to decide where a ridge ends. 
Overall a low quality mark, however I would identify this as I can get enough pairings I'm confident in.

Unable to follow ridges around mark reliably, so despite a lot of features being in the right place I have low confidence in proving they are in sequence.

Degree of similarity - 4
Degree of support - 3

High degree of similarity although there are a couple features in disagreement around the core area that I think could be down to an effect of deposition pressure. There are two differences, below pairing 20, in the unknown impression that I cannot give concise reasoning for. There is sweeping marks so obviously a bit of a shift in that area.
Upper are of the form has a slight shift.

There is so much in agreement with this mark but a couple differences that I am not happy with. The clarity of the mark is not great.

Support for inconclusive

Degree of Similarity - 4 Differences explainable by obvious distortion and are marked clearly along the line of distortion where the mark starts to twist and then drag off. Appear as possible feature on "cold analysis" but on comparison not true detail. Outside of this very low level of difference and therefore high level of similarity
Degree of Support - 5 taking cognisance of the distortion outside of this area there is high level of agreement and also high number of features available all in correspondence.

MARK IDENTIFIED TO REFERENCE PRINT. 1 DIFFERENCE NOTED BUT THINK THIS IS AN ERROR IN MY ANALYSIS AND A DISTORTED FEATURE IN MARK.

DEGREE OF SUPPORT 5
